.. activecode:: CS152_fruitco_selection_1
    :author: John Cigas
    :difficulty: 1
    :basecourse: thinkcspy
    :topic: Selection/Exercises
    :from_source: F

    A fruit company sells oranges for 32 cents a pound plus $7.50 per order for shipping.  If an order is over 100 pounds, then the shipping cost is reduced by $1.50.  Write a program that will ask the user for the number of pounds of oranges and then print the cost of the order.
    ~~~~